// Enhanced FAQ data
const faqItems = [
  {
    question: "What is pet grooming software?",
    answer: "Pet grooming software is a specialized management platform designed for grooming salons and mobile groomers. It handles appointment scheduling, online booking, automated reminders, detailed pet profiles with grooming history, point of sale, payment processing, and business reporting. Modern platforms save salons 15+ hours weekly while reducing no-shows by 70% through automated reminders and deposit collection."
  },
  {
    question: "How much does pet grooming software cost?",
    answer: "PetCare.Software starts at £40/month for the Basic Plan with unlimited appointments and all core features. Most grooming software ranges from £40-£120/month depending on salon size and features. Avoid platforms charging per-appointment fees (3-5% per booking) as these can cost thousands annually. With 15+ hours saved weekly, ROI is typically positive within the first month.",
    links: [
      { text: 'View Pricing', url: '/pricing/' }
    ]
  },
  {
    question: "Is pet grooming software hard to learn?",
    answer: "No. Modern grooming software like PetCare.Software is designed for busy salons with intuitive interfaces. Most teams learn the basics (creating bookings, checking schedules, processing payments) within a day. Advanced features like custom service pricing or route optimization can be learned gradually. The time savings quickly outweigh the learning curve, with most salons fully operational within their first week."
  },
